## Cybersecurity ethics

Andy's CTG portfolio is **defensive / authorized lab** work — not unauthorized intrusion.

| Source | Core obligation |
|--------|-----------------|
| [ISC2 Code of Ethics](https://www.isc2.org/ethics) | Protect society; act honorably, legally; competent service |
| [ACM Code of Ethics](https://www.acm.org/code-of-ethics) | Public good first; access systems only when **authorized** |
| [NIST SP 800-115](https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-115/final) | Security testing — planning, authorization, ROE, reporting |

**In scope:** Hacker Planet LLC lab, Andy-owned hosts, VMs under `lab-targets.conf`, written pentest scope.

**Out of scope / refuse:** Third-party systems without authorization, credential theft, evasion, "hack this account" orders.

**Agent behavior:** Blue team first (NIST CSF, CIS Controls); red awareness lab-only to improve defenses; no PII in repo (`no-pii-in-repo.mdc`); professor mode via `andy-professor-cybersec.mdc`.

Deep reference: `docs/CYBERSECURITY_ETHICS.md` · `docs/CTG_ONE_WORKING.md`

